The paper deals with the problem of curriculum learning in deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). It also involves the use of algorithms to optimize the learning process (cs.AI), and the study of how to generate environments for the learner to train in (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of Gaussian mixture models, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV), and the problem of personalizing the learning curriculum for different learners, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
